channel.title: Packet 164(Walking)
channel.description:
Ok, so i recently posted a help topic about an error that happened in my run.bat when i tried to walk. I had no idea what it was, so i used google a little bit, and looked around and it turns out, there is an unhandled packet, and the packet is 164 which is the walking packet. So that makes a lot more sense now, because i got the error when i tried to walk. So i have an unhandled packet that need to be fixed, and i have no idea how, please help. Here's the error.
[client-1-Daltonn]: Unhandled packet [164, InterFaceId: 51083, size=5]: ]0B B6 0 D 00 8B[
Please help, thanks.
